-- South Africa Routs Scotland 28-0 in International Rugby Match
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-11-17T17:33:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-17/south-africa-routs-scotland-28-0-in-international-rugby-match.html
South Africa  scored four tries as it
routed Scotland 28-0 in an international rugby match today.  Willem Alberts, Willie Le Roux and JP Pietersen went over
in the first half as the Springboks, No. 2 in the International
Rugby Board rankings, built a lead of 21-0 at Murrayfield in
Edinburgh.  Coenie Oosthuizen added a further try in the second half,
and Pat Lambie kicked all four conversions as ninth-ranked
Scotland was outplayed.  Yesterday, England lost 30-22 to top-ranked New Zealand,
Australia defeated Ireland 32-15,  Wales  routed Argentina 40-6,
France defeated Tonga 38-18 and Italy held off Fiji 37-31.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net  